dct_description_sm: Scale: 1:250000;  Projection: Lambert conical orthomorphic projection;  Map Type: lcgft;  Other Descriptive Notes about Map Series: Relief shown by contours, gradient tints, and spot heights.  Five classes of roads and four classes of railroads are shown.  Covers area north from southernmost tip of Bornholm [Denmark] to Belgard [Bialogard, Poland] to the south, and west from Heidebrink [Międzywodzie, Poland] to Neuwasser [Dąbki, Poland] to the east. Kolberg [Kołobrzeg, Poland] roughly at lower center portion of sheet.  Sheet O.55, Kolberg from set that includes various issues of some sheets, some by various survey units of the Allied Forces (A.F.) some reissued by U.S. Army Map Service, some sheets, G.S.G.S. 4346; some sheets A.M.S. M508 (G.S.G.S. 4346).  Heights in metres..  Military grid.  North European Zone III Grid. ... Spheroid: Bessel. ... Nord de Guerre Grid. ... Spheroid: Du Plessis..  Cataloging agency's copy printed on verso of portion of unrelated German map sheet, [Blatt Nr. 113], Reading and Newbury, from series with title: England 1:50 000, originally published [Berlin] : [Generalstab des Heeres], [1940]. German series consists of enlargements of the Ordnance Survey Popular Edition one-inch maps published by the German General Staff. Maps distributed by Army Map Service following capture from foreign military during World War II.  IXA.  Includes Convergence for corners of this sheet, To give a grid reference on this sheet, Index to adjoining sheets, Grid data, Conversion table, Glossary, Authorities, and Incidence of grid letters.
dct_isPartOf_sm: Field Maps of Colonel Roland T. Fenton
